Definition.WordDefinition:
SPRINT
List processing language involving stack operations. "SPRINT - A Direct Approach to List Processing Languages", C.A. Kapps, Proc SJCC 30 (1967). Sammet 1969, p 462.

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Sprint \Sprint\, n. The act of sprinting; a run of a short distance at full speed. [1913 Webster]
{Sprint race}, a foot race at the highest running speed; -- usually limited to distances under a quarter of a mile. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Sprint \Sprint\ (spr[i^]nt), v. i. [imp. & p. p. {Sprinted}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Sprinting}.] [Cf. {Sprunt}.] To run very rapidly; to run at full speed. [1913 Webster]
A runner [in a quarter-mile race] should be able to sprint the whole way. --Encyc. Brit. [1913 Webster]
sprint n : a quick run [syn: {dash}] v : run very fast, usually for a short distance
